net.sf.jclec.mo.evaluation

Class Objective

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.jclec.mo.evaluation.Objective
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, net.sf.jclec.IConfigure, net.sf.jclec.JCLEC
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    DTLZ1Objective, DTLZ2Objective, DTLZ3Objective, DTLZ4Objective, DTLZ5Objective, DTLZ6Objective, DTLZ7Objective, MOKnapsackObjective, MOTSPObjective, SymRegComplexity, SymRegError, ZDT1F1Objective, ZDT1F2Objective, ZDT2F1Objective, ZDT2F2Objective, ZDT3F1Objective, ZDT3F2Objective, ZDT4F1Objective, ZDT4F2Objective, ZDT5F1Objective, ZDT5F2Objective, ZDT6F1Objective, ZDT6F2Objective

    public abstract class Objective
extends java.lang.Object
implements net.sf.jclec.IConfigure
    An abstract objective function for multi-objective optimization problems. It maintains the properties about the domain and requires the implementation of an evaluation method over a candidate solution.

    HISTORY:

    • (AR|JRR|SV, 1.0, March 2018) First release.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Aurora Ramirez (AR), Jose Raul Romero (JRR), Sebastian Ventura (SV)

    Knowledge Discovery and Intelligent Systems (KDIS) Research Group: http://www.uco.es/grupos/kdis

    See Also:
    MOFitness, IConfigure, Serialized Form
